post_text: The fire department was called to AMS tonight for smoke in the building. It was not a fire but a problem with the oil in one of our boilers. The fire department shut off all breakers and shut down the defective boiler. We are in the process of assessing the situation further and will keep you updated as more information becomes available.

ATTENTION ATSD FAMILIES! During the month of October, in honor of the "Week of Respect", AMS staff and students will be creating a rock garden at the entrance to the school. We are asking for rock donations (3" to 5" inches) that our staff and students can use to paint inspirational message to be displayed in the garden. Any donations are greatly appreciated. Please drop them off in the main office by Monday, October 1st. THANK YOU!!

Joy Dominic, Principal AMS
